gate.creole.annic.apache.lucene.index

Class TermEnum

  • java.lang.Object
    • gate.creole.annic.apache.lucene.index.TermEnum
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FilterIndexReader.FilterTermEnum, MultiTermEnum, SegmentTermEnum

    public abstract class TermEnum
extends Object
    Abstract class for enumerating terms.

    Term enumerations are always ordered by Term.compareTo(). Each term in the enumeration is greater than all that precede it.

      • skipTo

        public boolean skipTo(Term target)
               throws IOException
        Skips terms to the first beyond the current whose value is greater or equal to target.

        Returns true iff there is such an entry.

        Behaves as if written: 

           public boolean skipTo(Term target) {
     do {
       if (!next())
             return false;
     } while (target > term());
     return true;
   }
        Some implementations are considerably more efficient than that.
        Throws:
        IOException
